<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06341110 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06341110 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  DRUG; CRIME; SUSPECT; SUICIDE  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  A former U.S. Drug Enforcement Administration informant swallowed a fatal doseof cyanide pills seconds after a jury convicted him of drug charges thatcarried a minimum 25-year prison sentence.;   His attorney said Donald WayneShantos, 53, feared retaliation in prison.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  CONVICTED OF DRUG CHARGES, DEA INFORMANT TAKESCYANIDE  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     As jurors were polled individually Wednesday to confirm the verdict,Shantos removed his false teeth and slid the cyanide tablets into his mouth.The tablets were in a glass vial in his pocket.;   Shantos slumped in hischair moments after taking the pills, breathing heavily and gurgling, and thenslid to the floor. He died about seven hours later.;   Jurors who convictedShantos of conspiracy and methamphetamine charges looked on in horror, U.S.Marshal Richard Cameron said.;   Under federal sentencing guidelines, U.S.District Judge Rudi M. Brewster would have had no choice but to sentenceShantos to 25 to 30 years in prison, defense attorney Craig Weinerman said.;  He even feared being placed in solitary confinement for his protection,Weinerman said.;   Shantos, a San Diego resident, had been free on $150,000bail. He left a note indicating he had taken a large amount of cyanide,Weinerman said.;   The note was dated Nov. 4, about the time his trial began.It said he planned to kill himself if convicted, Weinerman said.;   Shantoswas a part-time DEA informant from 1987 through 1990. His testimony in onecase helped put five people in prison, Weinerman said.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Associated Press  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  San Diego  </CITY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911206  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Friday  </DAY><MONTH>  December  </MONTH><PG.COL>  2A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  236  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Friday, December 6, 199100341110,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>